    Murphy, Hilltoppers Make It 8 Straight Wins Over Rival Vikings

    • Kevin Doyon doyonk@caledonian-record.com Staff Writer

      Kevin Doyon

      • Author email
    • Oct 23, 2022
    • Oct 23, 2022 Updated Oct 29, 2022
    • 0
    • Facebook
    • Twitter
    • WhatsApp
    • SMS
    • Email
    • Facebook
    • Twitter
    • WhatsApp
    • SMS
    • Email
    • Print
    • Save

    LYNDON CENTER — With time for one more snap before the half, St. Johnsbury senior quarterback Quinn Murphy turned a broken play into a Superman-esque diving touchdown — turning all momentum in the Hilltoppers’ favor and sending the Division I visitors well on their way to a 48-14 victory and an eighth straight victory over rival Lyndon in the 117th playing of The Game at Robert K. Lewis Field on Saturday.

    Lyndon’s RJ Kittredge rose up to bat down the Murphy pass attempt and, for a split second, looked to preserve the Vikings’ deficit at just 14-6.
